Hungary’s BUX Index Rises, Led by Advances in Gedeon Richter

-- B y   A n d r a s   G e r g e l y
-- 
2011-05-02T16:08:38Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-02/hungary-s-bux-index-rises-led-by-advances-in-gedeon-richter.html
Hungarian shares rose, as Gedeon
Richter Nyrt.,  Hungary ’s largest drugmaker, advanced the most
since April 20.  The benchmark BUX index of shares gained 0.5 percent to
24,272.08 by the 5 p.m. close in Budapest. Richter strengthened
1.5 percent to 37,870 forint. OTP Bank Nyrt., the country’s
largest lender, rose 0.5 percent.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Andras Gergely in Budapest at 
 agergely@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Gavin Serkin at 
 gserkin@bloomberg.net  